One person was killed and 10 others abducted by terrorists in two communities, in Igabi Local Government Area of Kaduna State. At Rido village, one person was killed, while two were abducted by the terrorists on Sunday night. A member of the joint task force in the area told DAILY POST that eight persons were abducted at Madauchi settlement, Kwarau ward of the Local Government Area. According to the member of the task force, the deceased was buried on Monday. The Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Mohammed Jalige could not respond to calls as of the time of filing this report.